sentences: Christel Martina Sundberg (born January 3, 1982), known by her stage name Chisu (Finnish pronunciation: [Ëˆkisu]), is a Finnish pop artist, songwriter, and producer.
The song was a hit in Finland in Spring 2008, peaking at number one on both the Singles Chart and the Downloads Chart and spending seven and nine weeks atop, respectively.

She released her second album Vapaa ja yksin on September 23, 2009.
Her third album, Kun valaistun, was released on October 5, 2011, through Warner Music Finland.
Another version of the album, entitled Kun valaistun 2.0 was released on June 6, 2012.
Her fourth album, Polaris was released on October 2, 2015.

In November 2012, Chisu was connected to a copyright controversy in Finland when a nine-year-old girl's home was raided by the police and had her laptop confiscated due to allegedly downloading Chisu songs.
